This paper deals with mechanism design and approximation algorithms for revenue maximization, which are topics typically studied in the subfield of computational game theory (cs.GT). The use of symmetric menu complexity as a measure of the complexity of a mechanism suggests that this paper may also be relevant to the subfield of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves the analysis of valuations and the design of algorithms, which are common themes in the subfields of algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the focus on revenue maximization and mechanism design suggests that this paper may also be relevant to the subfield of computational economics (cs.EC).
